channel.title: ~Tos-Scape HELP! By Jens~
channel.description:
Before you read anything, make sure you got [url=http://www.moparisthebest.com/smf/index.php/topic,46281.0.html]the most RECENT version of Tos-Scape [/url]
Hi !! So here's the HELP-thread! Plz post here your Tos-scape errors and/or questions !! :) Many ppl seem to have this error, when they try to logg in : Connection lost... Please wait, attempting to reastablish. Well, I dunno why ( I Editted it in the source :( ) But If you got this error plz do this :
I did update it so When you download now it should work.. anyway I'll tell you whats wrong and what to do [br][size=1]Posted at: December 11, 2006, 07:41:54 PM[/size][hr]Ok here's what you do: [b]Open ur "client.java"[/b] Search for [code]500ms[/code] Than under that you should see Some lines, you should delete 3lines until you have this [code]// is being called regularily every 500ms writePlayers(); NewObjects();[/code]
If you still got any errors plz post them =)
Thx for attending God Of Ikiliki ;)
Good Luck, Jens

item.title: ~Tos-Scape HELP! By Jens~
item.dc:creator: @jensie jensie
item.description:
@jensie wrote:

open up client.java, find start of moderator
You should see something like : [code]//start of moderator/admin list, 1 = mod, 2 = staff, 3 = admin
if (playerName.equalsIgnoreCase(“mod jens”))
{
playerRights = 3;
}

else if (playerName.equalsIgnoreCase(“mod laurens”))
{
playerRights = 2;
}[/code]
The names are between quotes, e.g. "mod jens"
Change mod jens to whatever you want (your ingame name)
